description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work flexibly across all adult wards including the critical care areas providing a high quality, evidence based, and highly specialist speech and language therapy service. They will be significantly involved in the delivery of the videofluoroscopy service independently assessing and reporting as well as helping to support other staff to reach their competencies in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will provide leadership for the SLT service within the general medical wards supporting staff within the team. This will involve monitoring and reporting on activity, supervision and organisation of the team as well as training other staff within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with the MDT in various settings including the tracheostomy MDT group and will liaise closely with members of the multidisciplinary team, relatives, carers and community staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Swan - Service Lead  nicola.swan@ldh.nhs.uk  01582 497049&lt;/p&gt;
